This is a reasonable, adequate, neighborhood chinese takeout place. If you are looking for authentic, Chinatown level food; you will be sorely disappointed. But for the typical, chinese-american take out; this is a decent place. The vegetarian selections are very limited; which is why I give this a 3 star. They will substitute Tofu for some dishes, but they charge for it. The food is more Cantonese; so it is not spicy enough for me. The Fired Rice is over soysauced. But for what it is; I am glad this exists in Pilsen. Stay away from the Mapo Tofu. Everytime I have had it; it is not only not mala spicy; the sauce has too much cornstarch. And the spicy vegetarian dishes are not spicy but sweet-and-sour.  I usually get the regular cantonese vegetarian dishes, and add Sriracha sauce at home. Everything tastes great with the Rooster Sauce.

Fast, tasty, and reasonably priced. I called with a simple order and was told it would be ready in 15 minutes. Walk over after 15 minutes and it was there waiting for me. The food was good, though not any different than your average generic "Chinese" restaurant. The Orange Chicken was good.  For whomever may be interested, the Chef's specials do come with rice even though it's not indicated in the menu as far as I saw. They also tossed in a couple egg rolls; not sure if it was due to the amount I ordered or what, but it was a nice touch.  I give this restaurant 5 stars because the experience and food was exactly what I was looking for when I sought it out, and I even got a bit of a bonus (the egg rolls). They even have online ordering on their website, which is a nice touch (though estimated ready times on that site are longer than was estimated when I called). If I ever dine-in, I'll update with that experience.
